{
  "texts": [
    "In this way, the doctor-patient relationship is built on trust in the medical process and its ability to justify itself at every step.",
    "However, the patient-doctor relationship is jeopardised once NNs become involved.",
    "With the current opaque AI, no reasons for a decision can be easily extracted.",
    "Thus, trust is undermined in two specific ways: (i) the trust that patients can have in healthcare professionals in general and (ii) the trust that medical doctors can have in the medical process itself.",
    "This generates a Trust Gap (TG) that needs to be crossed when a patient asks for a reason for a specific procedure, treatment or diagnosis."
  ]
}